<com id="com01008007"><bcv><xbr t="Ge 8:7-12">8:7–12</xbr></bcv> <b type="b_blue">a raven. … dove.</b> Ravens survive on a broad range of food types. If any food was available outside the ark, the raven could survive. In contrast, a dove is much more selective in its food choices. The dove's choice of food would indicate that new life had begun to grow; thus Noah and his family could also survive outside the ark.</com>
